<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> 
<crossway-bible>
	<book title="Matthew" num="39">
		<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016001">
		</marker>
		<chapter num="16">
			<heading
				>
				The Pharisees and Sadducees Demand Signs
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="1">
				<crossref let="f" cid="c40016001.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t40016001.1">
				</crossref>
				And the Pharisees and Sadducees came, and 
				<crossref let="g" cid="c40016001.2">
				</crossref>
				to test him 
				<crossref let="h" cid="c40016001.3">
				</crossref>
				they asked him to show them 
				<crossref let="i" cid="c40016001.4">
				</crossref>
				a sign from heaven.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016002">
			</marker>
			<verse num="2">
				He answered them,
				<note nid="n40016002.1">
				</note>
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="j" cid="c40016002.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					When it is evening, you say, 
					<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					It will be fair weather, for the sky is red.
					<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016003">
			</marker>
			<verse num="3" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					And in the morning, 
					<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					It will be stormy today, for the sky is red and threatening.
					<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					<crossref let="k" cid="c40016003.1">
					</crossref>
					You know how to interpret the appearance of the sky, but you cannot interpret 
					<crossref let="l" cid="c40016003.2">
					</crossref>
					the signs of the times.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016004">
			</marker>
			<verse num="4" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="m" cid="c40016004.1">
					</crossref>
					An evil and adulterous generation seeks for a sign, but no sign will be given to it except the sign of Jonah.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
				 So 
				<crossref let="n" cid="c40016004.2">
				</crossref>
				he left them and departed.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016005">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				The Leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="5">
				When the disciples reached the other side, they had forgotten to bring any bread.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016006">
			</marker>
			<verse num="6">
				Jesus said to them, 
				<woc
					>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Watch and 
					<crossref let="o" cid="c40016006.1">
					</crossref>
					beware of 
					<crossref let="p" cid="c40016006.2">
					</crossref>
					the leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016007">
			</marker>
			<verse num="7">
				And they began discussing it among themselves, saying, 
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				We brought no bread.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016008">
			</marker>
			<verse num="8">
				But 
				<crossref let="q" cid="c40016008.1">
				</crossref>
				Jesus, aware of this, said, 
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="r" cid="c40016008.2">
					</crossref>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					O you of little faith, why are you discussing among yourselves the fact that you have no bread?
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016009">
			</marker>
			<verse num="9" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="s" cid="c40016009.1">
					</crossref>
					Do you not yet perceive? Do you not remember 
					<crossref let="t" cid="c40016009.2">
					</crossref>
					the five loaves for the five thousand, and how many baskets you gathered?
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016010">
			</marker>
			<verse num="10" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					Or 
					<crossref let="u" cid="c40016010.1">
					</crossref>
					the seven loaves for the four thousand, and how many baskets you gathered?
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016011">
			</marker>
			<verse num="11" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					How is it that you fail to understand that I did not speak about bread? 
					<crossref let="o" cid="c40016011.1">
					</crossref>
					Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and Sadducees.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016012">
			</marker>
			<verse num="12">
				<crossref let="v" cid="c40016012.1">
				</crossref>
				Then they understood that he did not tell them to beware of the leaven of bread, but of 
				<crossref let="w" cid="c40016012.2">
				</crossref>
				the teaching of the Pharisees and Sadducees.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016013">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Peter Confesses Jesus as the Christ
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="13">
				<crossref let="x" cid="c40016013.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t40016013.1">
				</crossref>
				Now when Jesus came into the district of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, 
				<woc
					>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Who do people say that the Son of Man is?
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016014">
			</marker>
			<verse num="14">
				And they said, 
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Some say 
				<crossref let="y" cid="c40016014.1">
				</crossref>
				John the Baptist, others say 
				<crossref let="z" cid="c40016014.2">
				</crossref>
				Elijah, and others Jeremiah or one of the prophets.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016015">
			</marker>
			<verse num="15">
				He said to them, 
				<woc
					>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					But who do you say that I am?
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016016">
			</marker>
			<verse num="16">
				Simon Peter replied, 
				<crossref let="a" cid="c40016016.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				You are 
				<crossref let="b" cid="c40016016.2">
				</crossref>
				the Christ, 
				<crossref let="c" cid="c40016016.3">
				</crossref>
				the Son of 
				<crossref let="d" cid="c40016016.4">
				</crossref>
				the living God.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016017">
			</marker>
			<verse num="17">
				And Jesus answered him, 
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="e" cid="c40016017.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Blessed are you, 
					<crossref let="f" cid="c40016017.2">
					</crossref>
					Simon Bar-Jonah! For 
					<crossref let="g" cid="c40016017.3">
					</crossref>
					flesh and blood has not revealed this to you, 
					<crossref let="h" cid="c40016017.4">
					</crossref>
					but my Father who is in heaven.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016018">
			</marker>
			<verse num="18" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					And I tell you, 
					<crossref let="i" cid="c40016018.1">
					</crossref>
					you are Peter, and 
					<crossref let="j" cid="c40016018.2">
					</crossref>
					on this rock
					<note nid="n40016018.1">
					</note>
					 I will build my church, and 
					<crossref let="k" cid="c40016018.3">
					</crossref>
					the gates of 
					<crossref let="l" cid="c40016018.4">
					</crossref>
					hell
					<note nid="n40016018.2">
					</note>
					 shall not prevail against it.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016019">
			</marker>
			<verse num="19" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					I will give you 
					<crossref let="m" cid="c40016019.1">
					</crossref>
					the keys of the kingdom of heaven, and 
					<crossref let="n" cid="c40016019.2">
					</crossref>
					whatever you bind on earth shall be bound in heaven, and whatever you loose on earth shall be loosed
					<note nid="n40016019.1">
					</note>
					 in heaven.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016020">
			</marker>
			<verse num="20">
				<crossref let="o" cid="c40016020.1">
				</crossref>
				Then he strictly charged the disciples to tell no one that he was the Christ.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016021">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Jesus Foretells His Death and Resurrection
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="21">
				<crossref let="p" cid="c40016021.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t40016021.1">
				</crossref>
				From that time Jesus began to show his disciples that 
				<crossref let="q" cid="c40016021.2">
				</crossref>
				he must go to Jerusalem and 
				<crossref let="r" cid="c40016021.3">
				</crossref>
				suffer many things from the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be killed, and on 
				<crossref let="s" cid="c40016021.4">
				</crossref>
				the third day be raised.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016022">
			</marker>
			<verse num="22">
				And Peter took him aside and began to rebuke him, saying, 
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Far be it from you, Lord!
				<note nid="n40016022.1">
				</note>
				 This shall never happen to you.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016023">
			</marker>
			<verse num="23">
				But he turned and said to Peter, 
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="t" cid="c40016023.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Get behind me, Satan! You are 
					<crossref let="u" cid="c40016023.2">
					</crossref>
					a hindrance
					<note nid="n40016023.1">
					</note>
					 to me. For you 
					<crossref let="v" cid="c40016023.3">
					</crossref>
					are not setting your mind on the things of God, but on the things of man.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016024">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Take Up Your Cross and Follow Jesus
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="24">
				Then Jesus told his disciples, 
				<woc
					>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					If anyone would come after me, let him 
					<crossref let="w" cid="c40016024.1">
					</crossref>
					deny himself and 
					<crossref let="x" cid="c40016024.2">
					</crossref>
					take up his cross and follow me.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016025">
			</marker>
			<verse num="25" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					For 
					<crossref let="x" cid="c40016025.1">
					</crossref>
					whoever would save his life
					<note nid="n40016025.1">
					</note>
					 will lose it, but whoever loses his life for my sake will find it.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016026">
			</marker>
			<verse num="26" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					For 
					<crossref let="y" cid="c40016026.1">
					</crossref>
					what will it profit a man if he gains the whole world and forfeits his soul? Or 
					<crossref let="z" cid="c40016026.2">
					</crossref>
					what shall a man give in return for his soul?
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016027">
			</marker>
			<verse num="27" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="a" cid="c40016027.1">
					</crossref>
					For the Son of Man is going to come with 
					<crossref let="b" cid="c40016027.2">
					</crossref>
					his angels in the glory of his Father, and 
					<crossref let="c" cid="c40016027.3">
					</crossref>
					then he will repay each person according to what he has done.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v40016028">
			</marker>
			<verse num="28" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					Truly, I say to you, there are some standing here who will not 
					<crossref let="d" cid="c40016028.1">
					</crossref>
					taste death 
					<crossref let="e" cid="c40016028.2">
					</crossref>
					until they see the Son of Man 
					<crossref let="f" cid="c40016028.3">
					</crossref>
					coming in his kingdom.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
		</chapter>
	</book>
</crossway-bible>


